# Lab 8: Resource Allocation and Deadlock Avoidance
### Aim
Study resource allocation, deadlock conditions and Banker’s Algorithm for deadlock avoidance.

### Summary
Deadlock occurs when four necessary conditions hold: mutual exclusion, hold and wait, no preemption, circular wait.
Banker’s Algorithm checks system safe state before resource allocation to prevent deadlock and maintain system stability.

